        "manuscriptAbstract": "This protocol describes the drying of poly\\(ethylene glycol) \\(PEG) by a simple 6 step procedure. One can implement this protocol using common lab glass and lab equipment. Water is removed from PEG by azeotropic distillation in toluene. The two components are mixed and toluene and water are distilled off by heating the solution to 170\u00b0C.  This procedure can be implemented in ~2 h.",
